{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JnAafkYnowuYyUVBg8LSEu","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Beef Wellington.generated.18.txt"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9aab07eb-21b8-49fe-9f06-0a0b66a4125f","uuid":"554e7316-6e6a-4531-a73c-10aa26225a38","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Beef Wellington.generated.18.txt","content":"Dinner | Main Course\nPREPARATION 30 MIN | COOKING 45 MIN | DIFFICULTY: MEDIUM\n\nBeef Wellington\n\nTender beef surrounded by mushroom duxelles and puff pastry\n\nIngredients:\n- 1.2 kg beef tenderloin\n- 500g puff pastry\n- 400g mushrooms\n- 150g pâté\n- 2 shallots\n- 2 garlic cloves\n- 100g prosciutto slices\n- 2 egg yolks\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 tablespoon Dijon mustard\n\nMethod:\n1. Season the beef with salt and pepper\n2. Sear the beef in hot oil on all sides until golden\n3. Cool completely\n4. Prepare mushroom duxelles by chopping and cooking mushrooms with shallots\n5. Spread pâté on the cooked beef\n6. Cover with the mushroom mixture\n7. Wrap tightly with prosciutto slices\n8. Wrap the entire piece in puff pastry\n9. Brush with egg wash\n10. Bake at 200°C for 35-40 minutes until golden\n11. Rest for 10 minutes before slicing\n\nServes: 6-8 people\nWine pairing: Bordeaux or Burgundy","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
